sql:
SELECT DISTINCT prisoners.prisoner_id, prisoners.name 
FROM prisoners 
JOIN crime_statistics ON prisoners.prisoner_id = crime_statistics.prisoner_id;

SELECT name, capacity 
FROM prison_facilities 
WHERE capacity = (SELECT MAX(capacity) FROM prison_facilities);

SELECT name 
FROM prisoners 
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "Wanderers" refers to male prisoners;
- "Shine between the ages of a quarter-century and a third" refers to the age range 25 to 35;
- "Never found their place in the workforce nor a partner to share their journey" means they are both unemployed and single;
- "Fortresses" refers to prison facilities;
- "Of the most guarded kind" means high-security facilities;
- "Visits to these lands" refers to the number of times the prisoner has been transferred to or housed at a facility.

- Recidivism refers to a prisoner's tendency to commit another crime after being released.;
- The recidivism rate can be a measure for predicting the likelihood of reoffending.;
- In this context, the top 3 individuals are those with the highest calculated rates of recidivism among all prisoners.;

